{"id": "duc04-testb-20:7#21", "contents": "China is facing international criticism for its crackdown on democracy campaigners, and in an attempt to deflect this criticism, the country has sent a respected labor rights activist, Liu Nianchun, into exile in the United States. Liu was released from prison on medical parole, with authorities citing his poor health as the reason. However, human rights groups have denounced the move as cynical and manipulative, arguing that the Chinese government is playing \"hostage politics\" with no true commitment to international human rights standards."}
